      <section>
          <h3>What's the difference between my Credit Score and my Credit Report?</h3>
          <ul>
          	<li>Your Credit Score is a number lenders use to determine the interest rate to charge you</li>
          	<li>Your Credit Report lists all the interaction you've had with credit in the past</li>
          	<ul>
          		<li>Names/Addresses/Employers you've had in the past</li>
          		<li>Applications for credit (inquiries)</li>
          		<li>All credit extended to you for the past 10 years and your history of on time or late payment</li>
          		<li>Delinquencies</li>
          	</ul>
          </ul>
      </section>

