      <section>
        <h3>Credit Score - FICO vs FAKO</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>All 3 Credit Bureaus sell credit scores but these are not the credit scores banks use to determine creditworthiness</li>
            <li>FICO (formerly Fair Isaac Corp) takes your credit report from each CRA and calculates your FICO score based on their algorithm</li>
            <li>Each score is different because each bureau has different information on you</li>
            <li>When you apply for credit the bank will pull your credit report and FICO score from only one bureau</li>
          </ul>
